    "# How to do mesh-valued regression?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[KeOps] Warning : cuda was detected, but driver API could not be initialized. Switching to cpu only.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pyvista as pv\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import r2_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import FunctionTransformer, StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "import polpo.preprocessing.pd as ppd\n",
    "from polpo.models import ObjectRegressor\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing import (\n",
    "    IndexMap,\n",
    "    ListSqueeze,\n",
    "    Map,\n",
    "    NestingSwapper,\n",
    "    PartiallyInitializedStep,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.dict import DictMap, DictMerger\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.load.pregnancy import (\n",
    "    DenseMaternalCsvDataLoader,\n",
    "    DenseMaternalMeshLoader,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.conversion import ToVertices\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.io import PvReader\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.registration import PvAlign\n",
    "from polpo.sklearn.adapter import AdapterPipeline\n",
    "from polpo.sklearn.mesh import BiMeshesToVertices\n",
    "from polpo.sklearn.np import BiFlattenButFirst, FlattenButFirst"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "STATIC_VIZ = True\n",
    "\n",
    "if STATIC_VIZ:\n",
    "    pv.set_jupyter_backend(\"static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading meshes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "prep_pipe = PartiallyInitializedStep(\n",
    "    Step=lambda **kwargs: DictMap(PvAlign(**kwargs)),\n",
    "    _target=lambda meshes: meshes[list(meshes.keys())[0]],\n",
    "    max_iterations=500,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "subject_id = \"01\"\n",
    "\n",
    "file_finder = DenseMaternalMeshLoader(\n",
    "    subject_id=subject_id,\n",
    "    as_dict=True,\n",
    "    left=True,\n",
    "    struct=\"Hipp\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pipe = file_finder + DictMap(PvReader()) + prep_pipe\n",
    "\n",
    "meshes = pipe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading tabular data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "INFO: Data has already been downloaded... using cached file ('/home/luisfpereira/.herbrain/data/maternal/28Baby_Hormones.csv').\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pilot = subject_id == \"01\"\n",
    "\n",
    "pipe = DenseMaternalCsvDataLoader(pilot=pilot, subject_id=subject_id)\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pipe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here, we filter the tabular data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "session_selector = ppd.DfIsInFilter(\"stage\", [\"post\"], negate=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "predictor_selector = (\n",
    "    session_selector + ppd.ColumnsSelector(\"gestWeek\") + ppd.SeriesToDict()\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_dict = predictor_selector(df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create and fit regressor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Follow [How to perform dimensionality reduction on a mesh?](./mesh_dim_reduction.ipynb), we create a pipeline to transform the output variable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca = PCA(n_components=4)\n",
    "\n",
    "objs2y = AdapterPipeline(\n",
    "    steps=[\n",
    "        FunctionTransformer(func=np.squeeze),  # undo sklearn 2d\n",
    "        FunctionTransformer(inverse_func=ListSqueeze(raise_=False)),\n",
    "        BiMeshesToVertices(index=0),\n",
    "        FunctionTransformer(func=np.stack),\n",
    "        BiFlattenButFirst(),\n",
    "        StandardScaler(with_std=False),\n",
    "        pca,\n",
    "    ],\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tip: `polpo.models.Meshes2FlatVertices` is syntax sugar for the code above."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We get the data in the proper format for fitting and instantiate a regressor model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "((19, 1), 19)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dataset_pipe = (\n",
    "    DictMerger() + NestingSwapper() + IndexMap(lambda x: np.array(x)[:, None], index=0)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "X, meshes_ = dataset_pipe((x_dict, meshes))\n",
    "\n",
    "X.shape, len(meshes_)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = ObjectRegressor(LinearRegression(fit_intercept=True), objs2y=objs2y)"
   ]
  },
  {

    "## Evaluate fit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`model.predict` outputs meshes, but we know `LinearRegression` sees `PCA` components. We can evaluate [`r2_score`](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.metrics.r2_score.html) by applying transform.\n",
    "\n",
    "NB: these are values on the training data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tip: `objs2y` is available in `model.objs2y`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([0.04356306, 0.00644144, 0.24583473, 0.00145244])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "meshes_pred = model.predict(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "y_true = objs2y.transform(meshes_)\n",
    "y_pred = objs2y.transform(meshes_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "r2_score(y_true, y_pred, multioutput=\"raw_values\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.0743229168991969"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "r2_score(y_true, y_pred, multioutput=\"uniform_average\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This shows the model performs poorly. (NB: the goal of this notebook is not to find a great model, but to show how the analysis can be performed. Adapting the pipeline to use different models is a no-brainer.)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The analysis can also be done at a mesh level. The following assumes Euclidean distance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.048441950603014206"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 14,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "meshes2vertices = Map(ToVertices()) + np.stack + FlattenButFirst()\n",
    "\n",
    "r2_score(\n",
    "    meshes2vertices(meshes_),\n",
    "    meshes2vertices(meshes_pred),\n",
    "    multioutput=\"uniform_average\",\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [],

    "outputs_dir = Path(\"_images\")\n",
    "if not outputs_dir.exists():\n",
    "    outputs_dir.mkdir()\n",
    "\n",
    "gif_name = outputs_dir / \"regression.gif\"\n",
    "\n",
    "pl = pv.Plotter(\n",
    "    border=False,\n",
    "    off_screen=True,\n",
    "    notebook=False,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.open_gif(gif_name.as_posix(), fps=3)\n",
    "\n",
    "rendered_mesh = meshes_pred[0].copy()\n",
    "pl.add_mesh(rendered_mesh, show_edges=True)\n",
    "pl.add_title(f\"{(X_pred[0][0]):.0f}\")\n",
    "pl.write_frame()\n",
    "\n",
    "for index, mesh in enumerate(meshes_pred[1:]):\n",
    "    rendered_mesh.points = mesh.points\n",
    "    pl.render()\n",
    "\n",
    "    pl.add_title(f\"{(X_pred[index+1][0]):.0f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    pl.write_frame()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.close()"
   ]
